<p>I'm trying to set a common X and Y label for a grid of Matplotlib histograms plotted from a Pandas Data method. However it seems when the histogram is plotted it overwrites the labels.</p>  <p>How can I have common labels when using Pandas to plot histograms?</p>  <p>See example below</p>  <pre><code>import pandas as pd import matplotlib.pyplot as plt %matplotlib inline df = pd.read_csv("https://dataminingproject.googlecode.com/svn-history/r44/DataMiningApp/datasets/Iris/iris.csv")  # Setting up the figure fig = plt.figure(figsize = (14, 6)) ax = fig.add_subplot(111) ax.set_xlabel('common xlabel') ax.set_ylabel('common ylabel') </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/5mg19.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/5mg19.png" alt="Empty Plot"></a></p>  <p>As soon as I run the following line, the plots appear but the labels disappear</p>  <pre><code>df[["Sepal Length", "Species"]].hist(by = "Species", ax=ax) </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/eVuuG.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/eVuuG.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>I'm referencing this Stackoverflow thread <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/6963035/pyplot-axes-labels-for-subplots">pyplot axes labels for subplots</a></p>